      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start, helps with the structural side of things. but if we're looking at the actual raw data/crime rates, how much of that is actually just about the systemic stuff vs. actual behavioral patterns or cultural differences that might drive higher crime rates in those specific communities? just trying to see the full picture for the paper.",
